<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2151/39.</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Spanish
                                    Chargé</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Memorandum.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-17"><hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                        1907</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>The Acting Secretary of State has the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of the memorandum of the Spanish chargé d’affaires stating,
                                under the instruction of his Government, the action which the
                                Governments of Spain and France have found necessary to take in
                                order to suppress the disturbances at Casablanca without detriment
                                to the integrity of Morocco and the sovereignty of the Sultan.</p>
                            <p>The Government of the United States has taken due notice of the
                                communication.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>